 Milan Kundera, and Brassai,. Grenier offers here a series of observations and "ations that feel as spontaneous as good conversation, yet carry the lasting insights of a lifetime of reading and thinking. Palace of Books is rich with pleasures and surprises, the perfect accompaniment to old literary favorites, and the perfect introduction to new ones.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aEssayxAuthorship. 0aEssaysxAuthorship. 0aFrench literaturexHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aKaplan, Alice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaplan, Alice.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226232591423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226232591.jpg  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles